HEADWORD: Dis
<hw>Dis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<def>The god Pluto, god of the underworld; also called <altname>Dis
Pater</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dis</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: dis
<hw>dis</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[shortened from
<ets>dis</ets>respect.]</ety> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>dissed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>dissing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>to treat in a
disrespectful manner; to insult, disparage or belittle.</def>
<mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>disa</ent>⟦br⟧
